RIYADH: Saudi Arabia supports de-escalation efforts in Ukraine, a statement by the Saudi Cabinet  said Tuesday. The statement came during the Cabinet meeting headed by King Salman, Tuesday afternoon, at Al-Yamamah Palace in Riyadh. It emphasized Saudi Arabia’s “support for international efforts to reduce escalation in Ukraine through dialogue and diplomacy.” “This would contribute to restoring security and stability, and pave the way for discussions leading to a political solution to the crisis,” it added.